{%- comment -%}
  Marks a value that lives in stores.settings (NOT in the section's own config) as
  click-to-editable.

  Usage:
    <h1 {% render 'classic/snippets/editable-setting', key: 'heroTitle', value: settings.heroTitle %}>
      {{ slide_title }}
    </h1>

  Two editable channels exist because there are two places copy is stored, and they
  save through different actions:

    editable          -> pages.sections[i].settings   -> updatePageSections
    editable-setting  -> stores.settings              -> updateStoreSettings

  Same rule as `editable`: it emits the STORED value, never the rendered one. A
  hero with no heroTitle falls back to store.name, so the DOM shows a title while
  the setting is empty. Reporting the rendered text would silently freeze that
  fallback into the record the first time anyone clicked it.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- comment -%}
  Emits NOTHING outside the editor: these attributes carry the merchant's stored
  copy, and a visitor has no business receiving it.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- if editing -%}data-mcloud-setting="{{ key }}" data-mcloud-stored="{{ value | escape }}"{%- endif -%}
